Are you sure you dowloaded the Eclipse SDK and not the Eclipse RCP SDK? The
Eclipse SDK has around 84 plug-ins/fragments under the eclipse\plugins
directory. The RCP has less than 15.

How did you install Eclipse? Did you extract it to an empty directory or on top
of an existing install/non-empty directory?

On top of existing - when unzipping, responded "Yes to all" when asked to 
overwrite existing file.

That is the reason, then - this is not supported. See bug 68696 comment 8.

*** This bug has been marked as a duplicate of 68696 ***

I had searched through the bug database before submitting this bug - in hopes 
that someone had encountered the problem before - nothing turned up in my 
search.
